This is just my personal gripe, but I've not understood why `Deno.test` is not just a function imported like `assertEquals`?

E.g. instead of this:

```typescript
import { assertEquals } from "https://deno.land/std@0.145.0/testing/asserts.ts";

Deno.test("url test", () => {
  const url = new URL("./foo.js", "https://deno.land/");
  assertEquals(url.href, "https://deno.land/foo.js");
});
```

it could be:

```typescript
import { assertEquals, test } from "https://deno.land/std@0.145.0/testing/asserts.ts";

